We start by linking the relationships given:

• Janet is Michael’s ancestor.
• Michael is Jason’s ancestor.
• Jason is Dorothy’s ancestor.
• Dorothy is an ancestor of Theresa (since Theresa is Dorothy’s descendant).
• Theresa is an ancestor of Andrea (since Andrea is Theresa’s descendant).
• Andrea is an ancestor of Nicholas (because Nicholas is Andrea’s descendant).
• Nicholas is an ancestor of Frances (since Frances is Nicholas’s descendant).

When these relationships are chained together, we have:
Janet → Michael → Jason → Dorothy → Theresa → Andrea → Nicholas → Frances

This chain shows that Janet is an ancestor of Frances; equally, Frances is the descendant of Janet.

Therefore, the correct answer is:

<ANSWER>1</ANSWER>
